title: TCP/IP Collection Agent Input/Output Data and MIM - MediationZone Documentation 9.4 - InfoZone
text: Input/Output Data The Input/Output data is the type of data an agent expects and delivers. The agent produces UDRs in accordance with the Decoder tab. If Send Response is selected, the agent consumes bytearray types for single connections and TCPIPUDR for multiple connections. MIM The agent does not publish nor access any MIM parameters.
